feed.title: Fukushima Nuclear Station Monitoring by Homemade Geiger Counter using Geiger Bot Feed from iPad-3
feed.description:
*** CPM in Toyama measured by homebrew Geiger Counter ***
*** using SI-1G and SBM-20 Russian GM Tube ***

*Data Stream ID77:
 Feed from Homebrew Geiger counter using a Soviet-Russian GM tube SI-1G. 
 Background here; 14CPM at 0.06uSv/h.

*Data Stream ID78:
 Feed from Homebrew Geiger counter using a Soviet-Russian GM tube SBM-20. 
 Background here; 17CPM at 0.06uSv/h.

*Data Stream ID1: added on 1,Apr.2012
 Feed from Homebrew Geiger counter using a Soviet-Russian GM tube SBM-20.
 Measured its count by iPad-3 with "GeigerBot-APP", translate CPM to uSv/h.

*Data Stream ID2: added on 1,Apr.2012
 Feed from Homebrew Geiger counter using a Soviet-Russian GM tube SBM-20. 
 Measured its count by iPad-3 with "GeigerBot-APP". 

Both of above are placed Indoor, at 2F of the wooden house window side.The value of the CPM is NOT corrected by the specific-background counts and this data is NOT guaranteed at all for any situation.I put this data just for monitoring the tendency of the CPM in my house.
